Description: Foot of Attic pottery skyphos foot; glazed black inside and out; stand-ring reserved. On reserved underside of foot, two concentric circles, and graffito.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie
Bibliographic references: Venit 1988 / Greek Painted Pottery from Naukratis in Egyptian Museums (p. 112, no. 397, pl. 83)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1300)
